The paper deals with a variant of the nearest neighbor search problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The problem also has applications in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) due to its relevance in tasks such as image recognition and recommendation systems. The paper also presents a sampling technique that achieves a bi-criterion approximation, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
